Project: Simple Web Page

HTML Code:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Web Page</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header id="header">
    <h1>Welcome to My Web Page</h1>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>
  <main class="container">
    <section>
      <h2>About Me</h2>
      <p>Hello, I'm learning HTML and CSS. <span class="highlight">I'm excited to build more projects!</span></p>
      <img src="image.jpg" alt="An image on the page">
    </section>
    <aside>
      <h2>Related Links</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#">Link 1</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">Link 2</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </main>
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2023 My Web Page</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>


CSS Code (in style.css file):

body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

#header {
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
  padding: 20px;
  text-align: center;
}

.container {
  width: 80%;
  margin: auto;
}

.highlight {
  color: red;
  font-weight: bold;
}

img {
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  border-radius: 50%;
}

footer {
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px;
  text-align: center;
  clear: both;
}


Questions and Answers:

1. *Q: What is the purpose of the id attribute in HTML?*
    - A: The id attribute is used to specify a unique identifier for an element.

2. Q: How do you apply styles to multiple elements using CSS?
    - A: You can apply styles to multiple elements using the .class selector in CSS.

3. *Q: What is the difference between <section> and <aside> elements?*
    - A: The <section> element defines a self-contained section of related content, while the <aside> element defines content that is related to the main content, but not essential.

4. Q: How do you add an image to a web page using HTML?
    - A: You can add an image using the <img> tag, specifying the source of the image using the src attribute and alternative text using the alt attribute.

5. *Q: What is the purpose of the footer element?*
    - A: The footer element defines the footer section of a page or section, typically containing copyright information, contact details, and other secondary content.